rComments: Easily one of the best profs at this school! Super enthusiastic about the material, and always available for questions. I liked coming to school just so I could come to his lectures. Extremely caring, detailed, and loves to have discussions with his students in a knowledgeable and respectful manner!
He is very inspirational and a hiralrous person to learn from. The assignments were tough but were really informative.

He is hilarious and makes classes very fun and engaging. However, the readings are atrociously difficult. Almost no one in my class did the assigned reading for class participation. These make assignments brutal too. Guest lecturers are boring. The only prof with no late and paper-only submissions. Do NOT take his class for a bird course.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Good Professor who's pretty engaging and willing to get into debates with Students. He tries to keep his personal views out of discussions and mostly succeeds, but sometimes there's a bit of debate. He presented interesting topics and readings in the course and facilitated some great dialogue!

Terrible. Argues with students who offer alternate perspectives, only permits paper submissions during class with no late submissions, and assigns ridiculously pretentious readings for papers- the main difficulty is in wading through the poorly worded readings for assignments. Also has guest lecturers (fine) but keeps interrupting them.

Professor Fehige is a passionate man who cares about the subject matter as well as his students - so long as they actually try. If you put work into it (like any other course), you will do very well. Lectures are extremely useful and should not be forgone.
Vacuous, wordy and self-centered. My impression is that this "professor" tries very hard to cover up his emptiness and mediocrity.

Brilliant Professor! Cares very much about his students. He shows an interest in your academic development as well as your growth as a person. The diversity of his knowledge is unrivaled. You will rarely encounter someone in your life who knows so much about so many things.

entertaining but spastic - marked extra hard although not alot of assignments...accent was TERRIBLE!!!!! be prepared to get lost in his lectures as he doesnt follow a syllabus and is completely incomprehensible. cool glasses though
